y system.Eminently readable, provocative, and entertaining, this book is certain to consolidate Banham's reputation among architects and students of contemporary culture. For those acquainted with his writing, it offers welcome surprises as well as familiar delights. For those encountering Banham for the first time, it comprises the perfect introduction.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aArchitecture. 0aArt. 0aDesignxHistoryx20th century. 0aDesignxHistoryy20th century. 0aModernism (Art). 7aARCHITECTURE / History / General.2bisacsh1 aBanham, Mary, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBarker, Paul, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHall, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLyall, Sutherland, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPrice, Cedric, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520923201?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520923201423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520923201/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles